The paper discusses a technique for constructing a data structure to answer approximate near neighbor queries, which is a common problem in many areas of computer science such as data structures (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and data mining (cs.DM). The paper specifically focuses on the Indyk-Motwani Locality-Sensitive Hashing (LSH) framework, which is commonly used in these areas. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS, followed by cs.IT, cs.CV, cs.LG, and cs.DM.
